"pointer-events" CSS property is used by nodes to prevent text (NodeRendererItem) from receiving events.
   --> http://caniuse.com/#feat=pointer-events
   --> Part of CSS4 proposal... not officially supported?
   --> Affected browsers: IE (all), Opera (all)


"user-select" CSS property is used by nodes and the viewer background to prevent stuff from being selected.
   --> https://developer.mozilla.org/en/CSS/user-select
   --> Not officially part of any specification?
   --> Affected browsers: IE (9-), Opera (all)